Steps - 

1 - Ubuntu Server 20.*
2 - sudo apt update
3 - sudo apt install git
4 - sudo apt install nodejs -y
	sudo apt install npm -y
5 - sudo apt install nginx -y

6 - Remote access AWS EC2
	Steps -
		a. sudo adduser saurav
		b. sudo usermod -aG sudo saurav
		c.	su - saurav
		d.	mkdir .ssh
		e.	chmod 700 .ssh
		f.	touch .ssh/authorized_keys
		g.	chmod 600 .ssh/authorized_keys
		h.	ssh-keygen
		i.	cat .ssh/id_rsa.pub >> .ssh/authorized_keys
		j.  cat .ssh/id_rsa
		k. 	take the public key and save it in - C:\Users\Example\.ssh\aws-example-user.pem
		l.  # Read more about SSH config files: https://linux.die.net/man/5/ssh_config
			Host Ubuntu
				HostName <ip-address>
				User saurav
				IdentityFile C:\Users\Example\.ssh\aws-example-user.pem
				
		Connect and enjoy!
	
7 - CREATED Two application "backend" and "ui"
8 - Change nginx config file, /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
--> configuration for the ReactJS app
server {
        listen 80;
        server_name 3.7.55.52;
        root /home/saurav/CapstoneProjectGL/application/ui/build;
        index index.html;
        # Other config you desire (TLS, logging, etc)...
        location / {
                try_files $uri /index.html;
                }
        }

9 - In order to start the backend app
	cd /home/saurav/CapstoneProjectGL/application/backend
	python3 app.py --> cmd will start the application on the host ip @ 8080

backend: is an flask application
ui: React application which will consume the api's from the backend

